<section id="faq" aria-label="Vernal Medicare FAQs">
  <h2>Medicare in Vernal — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Which Medicare Advantage plans are available in Vernal and the Uintah Basin?</summary>
    <p>Availability changes each year. We compare current HMO and PPO options side-by-side for hospitals, doctors, and pharmacies around Vernal and the Basin and help you enroll if a plan fits.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Do local hospitals work with Medicare Advantage?</summary>
    <p>Many plans include nearby hospitals and clinics, but networks vary by plan. We verify your doctors and facilities before you switch so you're not surprised by out-of-network costs.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can you check my prescriptions and preferred pharmacy?</summary>
    <p>Yes. We run your medication list through each plan's formulary to estimate monthly costs and confirm preferred pharmacies in Vernal and surrounding towns.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>How much does your help cost?</summary>
    <p>There's no extra cost to you. We're licensed and paid by the plan you choose, and you get local support before and after enrollment.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>When can I change plans?</summary>
    <p>Initial Enrollment, Annual Enrollment (Oct 15–Dec 7), and certain Special Enrollment Periods may apply. We'll review your situation and the timing that fits.</p>
  </details>
</section>

